│ The bug is caused by an invalid transformation in `instcombine`. The pass attempts to sink │
│ a `shufflevector` instruction through a `select` instruction (`shuffle(select(c, v1, v2))  │
│ -> select(c, shuffle(v1), shuffle(v2))`). This transformation is generally valid, but it   │
│ fails to account for cases where the `shufflevector` changes the vector length.            │
│                                                                                            │
│ In the provided reproducer, the `select` operates on `<2 x float>` vectors with a `<2 x    │
│ i1>` condition. The `shufflevector` then transforms this `<2 x float>` vector into a `<4 x │
│ float>` vector. When `instcombine` pushes the shuffle through, it creates two new `<4 x    │
│ float>` vectors. It then incorrectly attempts to create a new `select` using the original  │
│ `<2 x i1>` condition with these new `<4 x float>` vectors. This violates a fundamental     │
│ LLVM IR rule: for vector `select` instructions, the condition vector must have the same    │
│ number of elements as the value vectors. This rule violation triggers an assertion and     │
│ crashes the compiler.                                                                      │
│                                                                                            │
│ To fix this, I will add a check in the `FoldOpIntoSelect` helper function within           │
│ `InstructionCombining.cpp`. This check will verify that the types of the newly generated   │
│ "true" and "false" value arms for the new `select` instruction are compatible with the     │
│ original `select`'s condition. Specifically, if the operation being folded changes the     │
│ vector length, the transformation will be aborted, preventing the creation of an invalid   │
│ `select` instruction.                                                                      │
│                                                                                            │
│ I will now apply this change.                                                              │
│                                                                                            │
